rows.label: qev092804_MSG0010
rows.name: Liesel...?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0020
rows.name:
Why'd you go AWOL?
Next time you get itchy feet, tell me.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0030
rows.name:
If it's a view you're looking for,
we can always hop in Hraesvelg.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0040
rows.name:
It's not meant for two, but, uh...
we can make do.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0050
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0060
rows.name:
Ha ha! If you insist.
Maybe we ought to develop a two-seater model![ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0070
rows.name: Yeah. I think I'd like that.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0080
rows.name: Although...I might not have it in me.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0090
rows.name: ...Yeah?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0100
rows.name: All right. Whatever you want.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0110
rows.name: ...You're not mad?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0120
rows.name: Why should I be mad at you?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0130
rows.name: ...You're strong, you know that?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0140
rows.name: I mean it...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_JNK0150
rows.name: Advise

rows.label: qev092804_SEL0160
rows.name: Tell her she shouldn't have to push herself.

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0170
rows.name: Absolutely. When the going gets tough, go slow.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_JNK0180
rows.name: Question

rows.label: qev092804_SEL0190
rows.name: Ask if she's going to give up here.

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0200
rows.name: Of course that isn't anyone's first choice.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0210
rows.name: But...I don't see the point in having to suffer for the work.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0220
rows.name: ...That's not it.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0230
rows.name: So...you're OK to keep going?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0240
rows.name:
The variable flight system's complete—
we basically solved the power fluctuation lag.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0250
rows.name: Say the word and I'll hop straight in, no sweat—[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0260
rows.name: No, you don't get it![ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0280
rows.name: All right, what did the boss say to you?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0300
rows.name:
I knew it. What did he make you do?
Come on, talk to me, Leesh.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0310
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0320
rows.name: It's my fault...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0330
rows.name: The deception... I was part of it...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0340
rows.name: What...?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0350
rows.name: What "deception" are you talking about?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0360
rows.name: ...When Hraesvelg enters cruise mode...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0370
rows.name:
You know how we configured the engine?
To transform with the Skell?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0380
rows.name:
Well, yeah... Of course. Without that, there's no way
you could possibly maintain the right level of thrust.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0390
rows.name:
Right. Typical engine structure couldn't take it.
In cruise mode, the thrust would be far too extreme.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0400
rows.name:
Well, we never implemented that feature.
That was what was decided.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0410
rows.name:
Wha—?! They can't do that...
The whole damn Skell could fall apart![ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0420
rows.name: No... That bastard...![ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0430
rows.name:
He said...he wanted to...
keep manufacturing costs down.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0440
rows.name:
It's completely unacceptable, I know.
Waving it through would lead to horrific accidents.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0450
rows.name: I, uh— Of course, I tried to change his mind.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0455
rows.name: Really...I tried.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0460
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0470
rows.name:
But he said... "You don't want to end up
like your predecessor, do you?"[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0480
rows.name: Predecessor...?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0490
rows.name:
Wh-? You mean...
that incident wasn't a suicide?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0500
rows.name: In the Hraesvelg prototype's test flight...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0510
rows.name: The crash...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0520
rows.name:
...It was because of an error in the code.
It was an accident waiting to happen.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0530
rows.name: I know...because I doctored that code.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0540
rows.name:
The former chief caught wind of it,
and tried to report me.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0550
rows.name:
But then, the boss stepped in.
That's when...he had his suicide staged.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0560
rows.name: Oh God... Alicia...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0570
rows.name:
He couldn't afford for the project to be delayed.
If word got out, it might've been scrapped...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0580
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0590
rows.name: And now...you're looking the other way again?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0600
rows.name: I'm sorry. What I've done is beyond forgiveness.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0610
rows.name:
But even though I knew I was complicit in his crime...
there was no turning back.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0620
rows.name:
If nothing else, I wanted to see it through.
To finish it for you...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0630
rows.name: Our gifted fighter pilot.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0635
rows.name: I wanted...to witness the heights you could soar to...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0640
rows.name: How could you...? I trusted you, Leesh.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0650
rows.name:
I thought as long as we were together,
we could do anything.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0655
rows.name: But...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0660
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0670
rows.name: After hearing all this, I can't unhear it.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0680
rows.name: What he's done...and what you've done...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0690
rows.name: I know.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0700
rows.name: You're good. I figured this was how you'd react.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0710
rows.name:
You've always walked the path you believe in.
And you've never strayed from it, not once.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0720
rows.name:
Everything I've done,
all of the boss's schemes...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0730
rows.name: It's all here, recorded on my comm device.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0735
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0740
rows.name:
Part of me wanted to leave this and die—
that way, someone else could handle the fallout.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0750
rows.name:
You know I...
I won't be able to forgive you right away.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0760
rows.name: I know.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0770
rows.name: But...then again...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0780
rows.name: The fact you're still here, alive...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0785
rows.name: I'm... I'm so glad.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev092804_MSG0790
rows.name: Liesel...[ST:wait ]
